  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Missouri totaled $8.3B in FY2026 to date; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). AwardCount was 84,576 and averageAwardSize was $98.5K, while obligations were down 40.4% year over year. The Department of Defense and Department of Energy were the largest buyers, with the Department of Defense accounting for $5.5B and the Department of Energy accounting for $2B in obligations. THE BOEING COMPANY and HONEYWELL FEDERAL MANUFACTURING & TECHNOLOGIES, LLC were the largest vendors by dollar volume, at $3.5B and $2B respectively, and THE BOEING COMPANY also appears with a separate $625M entry. At the industry level, Aircraft Manufacturing and Facilities Support Services led obligations with $2.4B and $2.1B respectively, followed by Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $642M and Ammunition (except Small Arms) Manufacturing at $633M. Historical fiscal-year totals show variability: FY21 was $13.3B, FY22 was $11.2B, FY23 was $15.6B, FY24 was $16.2B, and FY25 was $14B.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has Missouri federal contracting changed year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations were down 40.4% year over year in FY2026 to date. TotalObligations in FY2026 to date were $8.3B, compared with prior fiscal-year totals of $14B in FY25, $16.2B in FY24, $15.6B in FY23, $11.2B in FY22, and $13.3B in FY21. The current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). AwardCount was 84,576 with an averageAwardSize of $98.5K for the partial FY2026 period."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, industries, and vendors lead FY2026 contracting in Missouri?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense led buying with $5.5B, followed by the Department of Energy at $2B; other top buyers include the Department of Veterans Affairs at $194M and the Department of Agriculture at $185M. Top industries were Aircraft Manufacturing at $2.4B and Facilities Support Services at $2.1B, with Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $642M and Ammunition (except Small Arms) Manufacturing at $633M. THE BOEING COMPANY was the largest vendor entry at $3.5B, HONEYWELL FEDERAL MANUFACTURING & TECHNOLOGIES, LLC followed at $2B, and other major vendors included EVERNORTH FEDERAL SERVICES INC at $642M and WORLD WIDE TECHNOLOGY LLC at $133M."
      }
    ]
  },
